{"article_id":"p2ZuDqEwDlWHY5tr","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu arrives in the US today with an unenviable task :","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"arguing","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"that President Obama should be skeptical of Iran 's intentions ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"even as the world cheers its extraordinary change of tune .","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"\" I think","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Netanyahu is a spoiler","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"he comes to a party","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"he wasn ' t invited to ,","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"and he ' s going to ruin the party , \"","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"says Yoel Guzansky , a researcher at the Institute for National Security Studies","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"( INSS )","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"in Tel Aviv","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"who served as an adviser on Iran ' s nuclear program to previous prime ministers .","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"But some say","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Mr. Netanyahu ,","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"who meets with President Obama at the White House today ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"sees himself as playing a Churchillian role","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"to alert the world to the dangers of appeasement ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"just as the formidable British leader did","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"when faced by the Nazi regime .","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"For one","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"who sees the Iranian nuclear issue in existential terms ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"being perceived as a party pooper is a small price to pay .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Perhaps to prove its point ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"Israeli intelligence disclosed yesterday","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"that earlier this month it arrested a Belgian businessman of Iranian descent","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"for spying on Israel .","depth":9},{"id":28,"text":"And Israel is not alone .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"Other US allies in the Middle East are also deeply concerned by the Obama administration ' s perceived naïvete , weakness , and desperation for a foreign policy success in the region","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that could well come at their own expense .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Obama 's readiness","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"to support Egypt 's mass uprising against President Hosni Mubarak in 2011","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"was seen by Saudi Arabia and others as abandoning a 30-year ally ;","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"his lack of decisiveness and concrete action on Syria ,","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"which has partially become a proxy war for regional interests","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"left regional powers to duke it out on their own ;","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"and now the rush","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"to embrace Iran","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"before anything has changed on the ground","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"is adding to such concerns .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"\" I think","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"Israel and some of the Arab countries , especially in the Gulf , are very worried today , \"","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"says Mr. Guzansky ,","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"who specializes in regional dynamics","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"and frequently travels to the Gulf .","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"\" They are very much afraid of a US-Iran understanding","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"that will give Iran some sort of immunity in the region . \"","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"It ' s not just the nuclear program that is of concern .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"Even if the US manages to strike a deal on that question ,","depth":8},{"id":50,"text":"there is still the issue","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"of Iran sponsoring terrorist groups such as the Lebanese Shiite movement Hezbollah on Israel ' s northern border and Palestinian Hamas on its southern flank .","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"It was not always like this .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Like the US , Israel had strong common interests with Iran up until the 1979 Islamic Revolution ,","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"when the Western-backed Shah was overthrown","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"and replaced with a Grand Ayatollah","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"who saw himself as carrying out the will of God .","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"But Israel has never been a country","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"to trust others , especially on security issues .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"In that sense it is more similar to its Arab neighbors ,","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"says Efraim Inbar , director of the Begin-Sadat Center for Strategic Studies at Bar-Ilan University .","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"\" Israel doesn ' t trust anybody , not even the American president , \"","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"Mr. Inbar says .","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"\" A word doesn ' t mean anything .","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"Not even a signed paper .","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"So it ' s a big gap between how liberal Americans think about international relations and how Israelis and Arabs [ see it ] . \"","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"A key issue","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"that has led to Israeli distrust in the Iranian regime","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"is a pattern","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"of Iranian leaders","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"denying or minimizing the Holocaust .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Though President Hassan Rouhani last week made a significant departure from his predecessor Mahmoud Ahmadinejad ' s repeated denials of the Holocaust ,","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"some saw him merely softening the language","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"- and suspected him of doing the same with the Iranian nuclear program .","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"\" My grandmother was gassed at Auschwitz .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"My grandfather died of typhus in Theresienstadt .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"My aunts and uncles , on both my mother and father ' s side , were exterminated in Sobibor , Majdanek , and Belzec , along with nine of their children , my first cousins , all under the age of seven , \"","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"wrote Haaretz journalist Chemi Shalev .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"`` [ It is ] certainly valid to note that [ Iran ] may be playing the same game with their nuclear weapons program","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"as they are with their refusal to accept the Holocaust .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"That just as they are couching their anti-Semitism in more palatable terms ,","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"so they are repackaging Iran ' s continued drive","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"to produce nuclear weapons in words","depth":9},{"id":83,"text":"that spark less suspicion","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"and elicit less scrutiny . \"","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"Last year Netanyahu came marching to the United Nations General Assembly with a cartoon drawing of a nuclear bomb , and a clear red line","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"cutting across it .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"His speech , as in previous years , was forceful","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"and followed a summer","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"of threatening to attack Iran unilaterally","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"if the US decided","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"it was unready to join forces with Israel","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"to stop Iran 's suspected development of nuclear weapons .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"This year , Netanyahu has much less leverage .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Any military action would be seen as spoiling diplomatic efforts ,","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"and the diplomacy is unlikely to include Israel in a meaningful way .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"So he has pledged to simply `` tell the truth '' about Iran 's intentions .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"`` I will tell the truth in the face of the sweet talk and the onslaught of smiles , ''","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"he said yesterday","depth":12},{"id":99,"text":"before departing for the US .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"`` One must talk facts","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"and one must tell the truth .","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"Telling the truth today is vital for the security and peace of the world","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"and , of course , it is vital for the security of the State of Israel .","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"So the best","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Netanyahu may be able to do at the White House today is to suggest ways","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"that the US and other Western powers can keep the pressure on Iran","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"while pursuing the diplomatic track .","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"\" Israel should ...","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"[ tell ] them","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"look ,","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"they are buying for time ,","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"we need to do this and that , \"","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"including removing enriched uranium from Iran and closing the enrichment plant Fordow ,","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"says Guzansky of INSS .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"But Netanyahu should make clearer","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"that he ' s willing to give diplomacy a chance under the right conditions ,","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"he says .","depth":6},{"id":118,"text":"Indeed ,","depth":4},{"id":119,"text":"even though concern about Iran is an issue","depth":6},{"id":120,"text":"that crosses almost all political lines in Israel ,","depth":6},{"id":121,"text":"some are cautiously optimistic about the change in rhetoric of the past week .","depth":5},{"id":122,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":123,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":124,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":125,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":126,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":127,"text":"\" Even if Iran will hold nuclear power with reasonable leadership ,","depth":6},{"id":128,"text":"that is worrying , \"","depth":6},{"id":129,"text":"admits Alon Liel , a veteran Israeli diplomat ,","depth":5},{"id":130,"text":"reflecting widespread views","depth":5},{"id":131,"text":"that a nuclear-armed Iran could dictate regional dynamics .","depth":5},{"id":132,"text":"\" Still , I think","depth":5},{"id":133,"text":"it ' s an improvement","depth":6},{"id":134,"text":"that we have leaders","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"[ like Rouhani ]","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"that address the world ,","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"that want to communicate with the world .","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"\" I feel","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"also a big opportunity here , \"","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"he adds .","depth":6},{"id":141,"text":"\" I think","depth":7},{"id":142,"text":"if everybody in the world would react like Netanyahu","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"and everybody would say ,","depth":10},{"id":144,"text":"' It ' s a bluff ,","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"it ' s a bluff , '","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"then nothing would happen .","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"So I ' m glad","depth":7},{"id":148,"text":"that a big part of the world , especially Obama , is welcoming it . \"","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":297,"left":270,"right":296,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":270,"left":233,"right":269,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":233,"left":176,"right":232,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":162,"right":175,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":162,"left":152,"right":161,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":152,"left":0,"right":151,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":151,"left":150,"right":3,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":161,"left":157,"right":160,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":4,"right":156,"relation":